  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Women with Obstetric Fistula in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">From May 2019 &#x2013; May 2022, Amref UK is running a project to empower women through the treatment of obstetric fistula. This will be through a partnership between Amref Health Africa UK, Amref Health Africa Tanzania, Magu Poverty Focus on Older People Rehabilitation Centre (MAPERECE) and Comprehensive Community Based Rehabilitation in Tanzania (CCBRT) for women in rural and urban Tanzania. This will lead to improved access to high quality fistula treatment. The psychosocial support will facilitate the social reintegration of women in the community after fistula repair surgery. The skills training and livelihood opportunities provided will enable social and economic empowerment long-term.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support 180 women to receive quality obstetric fistula repair services at Bugando Medical Centre in Mwanza and CCBRT in Dar es Salaam; Provide psychosocial support for 150 women and their families; Provide entrepreneurship training and livelihood opportunities for 180 women after fistula repair surgery to promote their social reintegration.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will enable 180 women and girls with fistula to receive free fistula repair treatment, psychosocial support and livelihoods training and opportunities for social reintegration. 900 family members (on average five members per household) will also receive information and psychosocial support through home visits.</narrative>
  </description>
